    "Define inclusion and exclusion criteriaInclusion and exclusion criteria are essential for ensuring objectivity and consistency in selecting studies for this systematic literature review (SLR).",
    "These criteria were carefully designed to align with the study's research objectives and ensure the quality and relevance of the included studies.",
    "Inclusion criteriaThe following inclusion criteria were applied to select studies:• Time Frame (2018-2023): Studies published within this period were included to reflect recent advancements and trends in the use of LLMs in education.",
    "This ensures the review captures up-to-date research and emerging insights.",
    "• Language (English): Only studies written in English were included to maintain consistency in interpretation and analysis.• Focus on LLMs in Education: The selected studies must specifically address the application of LLMs, including ChatGPT, in the educational domain."
